KODRIXIDE SOURCE-AVAILABLE LICENSE 
1. OWNERSHIP & ANTI-COPY PROTECTION
The source code, logic, and branding of KodrixIDE are the sole intellectual property of Zohaib.

No Redistribution: You may not host, mirror, or redistribute this source code on any platform (GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket, etc.) as your own.

No Plagiarism: You are strictly forbidden from "copy-pasting" significant portions of this logic into competing IDE projects.

Reverse Engineering: You may not decompile or reverse-engineer the compiled binaries of KodrixIDE for commercial gain.

2. COMMERCIAL DEPLOYMENT & REVENUE TRIGGER
KodrixIDE follows a "Test for Free, Pay to Earn" model.

Free Use: Local development, educational learning, and private testing are 100% free.

Deployment Trigger: Any public deployment of a service using KodrixIDE code requires a license.

The Earning Rule: If your deployment generates any revenue (via ads, subscriptions, or sales), you must purchase a Commercial License from Zohaib.

3. MANDATORY ATTRIBUTION
Every project built with or powered by this software must include the following in its documentation and "About" section:

"Powered by KodrixIDE by Zohaib"
A direct link to the original KodrixIDE GitHub repository must be provided.

4. TERMINATION
If you violate any of these terms (e.g., you deploy for profit without paying, or you remove the attribution), your license to use the software is automatically terminated. You must then delete all copies of the code and any active deployments.

5. NO WARRANTY (THE "AS IS" SHIELD)
THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND. THE AUTHOR (ZOHAIB) SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY DATA LOSS, HARDWARE DAMAGE, OR LEGAL ISSUES ARISING FROM THE USE OF THIS SOFTWARE. YOU USE KODRIXIDE AT YOUR OWN RISK.

🛠️ Why this update matters:
Termination Clause: This gives you the legal right to shut them down the moment they stop following your rules.

Reverse Engineering: This protects you if you ever decide to release a compiled version of the app.

Revenue Clause: It clearly defines that "Ads" count as earning, so they can't claim it's "free" just because they aren't charging users directly.
